CSS: Cascading Style Sheets

CSS is a stylesheet language used to describe the prtesentation of a document written in HTML or XML. CSS describe how element should be rentered on screen, on paper, in speech or on other media.

CSS is along the core language of the core web and is standardized across web browers according to W3C specifications. Previously, development of various parts of css specification was done synchonously, ehich allowed versioning in the latest recommended version.
We have heard about CSS1, CSS2 and CSS3. however css4 has never become an official version.